{"questionId":"12408","questionHtml":"<p>Find a 90 % confidence interval for&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\mu \">\n  <mi>μ</mi>\n</math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>90 % confidence interval is&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"1.998 \\pm 1.660\\sqrt {\\frac{{0.0869}}{{100}}} \">\n  <mn>1.998</mn>\n  <mo>±</mo>\n  <mn>1.660</mn>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>0.0869</mn>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>100</mn>\n      </mrow>\n    </mfrac>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>= (1.95, 2.05)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> <em><strong>FT</strong></em> their <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\sigma \">\n  <mi>σ</mi>\n</math></span> from (c).</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Condone the use of the <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"z\">\n  <mi>z</mi>\n</math></span>-value 1.645 since <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"n\">\n  <mi>n</mi>\n</math></span> is large.</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Accept any values that round to 1.95 and 2.05.</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12408","referenceCode":"19M.3.AHL.TZ0.Hsp_3d","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find a 90 % confidence interval for μ .","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.14—Linear transformation of a single RV, E(X) and VAR(X), unbiased estimators","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.15—Central limit theorem","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.